Former President Glafcos Clerides of Cyprus passed away on November 18, 2013. He was known for his dedication to public service, human rights, international cooperation, and peace. President Clerides played a significant role in leading Cyprus to independence and restoring constitutional order during the violence in 1974. He also provided support and sympathy when two individuals were killed at the American Embassy in 1974. President Clerides worked tirelessly to reunify Cyprus and bring the island into the European Union. The United States, including President Obama, extends their condolences on his passing.